title: Polk County checklist of the observations of members of the Des Moines Audubon Society
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Polk County checklist, field trips record, of the observations of members of the Des Moines Audubon Society compiled by Woodward H. Brown, November 1973. The checklist covers several topics, including the following: statistical records 1959-1973, field observation report forms and birding maps.

title: Observations and data on various birds by Woodward Hart Brown (part 2 of 3)
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: A collection of bird sightings around Iowa compiled by Woodward Hart Brown, including notes, correspondence, and photographs. This document is part two of three and begins with the tabbed section labeled Sandpiper and ends with the tabbed section labeled Nuthatch/Shrike.

title: Annotated copy of Polk County checklist of the observations of members of the Des Moines Audubon Society, 1953

description: Polk County checklist of the observations of members of the Des Moines Audubon Society compiled and prepared by Woodward H. Brown, November 1953. The document includes handwritten annotations by Woodward H. Brown and covers bird migration, locations and species.

title: Annotated copy of Polk County checklist of the observations of members of the Des Moines Audubon Society, 1959
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Polk County checklist, field trips record, of the observations of members of the Des Moines Audubon Society compiled by Woodward H. Brown, November 1959. The document includes handwritten annotations by Woodward H. Brown and covers several topics: bird migration, bird field trip sightings, dates sighted and a birding map.

title: Checklist of birds by state and country
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Checklist of birds by state and country compiled by Woodward H. Brown. The checklist covers multiple states, countries and many different species of birds.
subject: Bird watching;Birds--Geographical distribution;Birds--Research;Cranes, Rails, and Coots (Gruiformes);Doves and Pigeons (Columbiformes);Ducks, Geese, and Swans (Anseriformes);Pelicans, Cormorants, Darters, and Frigate-birds (Pelecaniformes);Grebes (Podicipediformes);Hawks, Eagles, Falcons, Osprey, and Vultures (Falconiformes);Herons, Bitterns, Egrets, Ibises, and Storks (Ciconiiformes);Loons (Gaviiformes);Perching-birds and songbirds (Passeriformes);Shore-birds, Gulls, and Auks (Charadriiformes);Quails, Pheasants, Turkeys, and Grouse (Galliformes);Woodpeckers and allies (Piciformes);Owls (Strigiformes);Swifts and Hummingbirds (Apodiformes);Cuckoos, Roadrunners, and Anis (Cuculiformes);Nighthawks and Nightjars (Caprimulgiformes);Kingfishers (Coraciiformes)

title: Bird checklist by Woodward Hart Brown (part 3 of 3)

title: Bird checklist by Woodward Hart Brown (part 1 of 3)
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Sighting notes for bird species compiled by Woodward Hart Brown with date of sightings. This document is part one of three and begins with the tabbed section labeled Gulls/Terns and ends with the tabbed section labeled Mimic Thrushes.

title: Observations and data on various birds by Woodward Hart Brown (part 1 of 3)
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: A collection of bird sightings around Iowa compiled by Woodward Hart Brown, including notes, correspondence, articles, and photographs. This document is part one of three and begins with the tabbed section labeled Loons/Grebes and ends with the tabbed section labeled Rails/Plovers.
subject: Bird watching;Birds--Eggs;Birds--Nests;Cranes, Rails, and Coots (Gruiformes);Ducks, Geese, and Swans (Anseriformes);Grebes (Podicipediformes);Hawks and Eagles (Accipitridae);Herons, Bitterns, Egrets, Ibises, and Storks (Ciconiiformes);Loons (Gaviiformes);Plovers (Charadriidae);Quails, Pheasants, Turkeys, and Grouse (Galliformes)

title: Bill Youngworth letter to Woodward Hart Brown regarding general bird notes, May 17, 1963
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Letter from Bill Youngworth to Woodward Hart Brown dated May 17, 1963. Youngworth states that publishing general bird notes is a good way for people who don't write full articles to get a byline in ornithology periodicals. He laments that the current editor of Iowa Bird Life does not publish as many as the previous editor did, and that the Wilson Bulletin no longer publishes any at all. Youngworth also discusses the ebb of native bird life.

title: Bill Youngworth letter to Woodward Hart Brown regarding a new editor for Iowa Bird Life, January 10, 1961
contributing_institution: Iowa State University. Special Collections and University Archives
description: Letter from Bill Youngworth to Woodward Hart Brown dated January 10, 1961. Youngworth congratulates Brown for his work on the five year index for Iowa Bird Life (vol. 30, no. 4) and says that he hopes that Brown will become the new editor of Iowa Bird Life. Youngworth also discusses his winter field work and describes his search for Red Crossbills.
